    "body": "When freshly compiling two .pyx + the required .pxd file, each containing a cdef class definition and one of them importing the other class to use it, a ValueError is thrown at runtime ''if and only if the two are part of a package'' and have been compiled with an old style setup script.\n\n- reproduce:[attached testcase file to a directory on your PYTHONPATH[[BR]([BR]]\nextract)]\nbuild with \"python setup.py build_ext --inplace\"[\"python test.py\"\n\n- expected:\nPASS\n\n- actual:[[BR]([BR]]\nrun)]\n~/bitbucket/tc_valueerror >python test.py[(most recent call last):\n  File \"test.py\", line 3, in <module>\n    from tc_valueerror import problemreader\n  File \"node.pxd\", line 1, in init problemreader (problemreader.c:895)\n    cdef class Node:\nValueError: tc_valueerror.node.Node has the wrong size, try recompiling\n\n- note:[[BR]([BR]]\nTraceback)]\nthe problem occurs on fresh compiles without any modification to the source; the problem does not reproduce if the .pyx files aren't part of a package. When running \"cython -a *.pyx\" before running the setup script, everything works fine.\n\nAt 2011-08-09T13:11:40Z **santa** added attachment [tc_valueerror.tar.bz2](https://gist.github.com/57fa3dc7413bf3f6f69138d602f6bccc)\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/709",
